==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saccharonic
<hw>Sac`cha*ron"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or derived from, saccharone; specifically,
designating an unstable acid which is obtained from saccharone
<sd>(a)</sd> by hydration, and forms a well-known series of
salts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saccharose</ent>⟦br⟧
